strategies: I just tried to be quick so that the names would stay fresher in my short term memory. I also tried to associate countries or states to the names to help remember if I had seen it before.
familiar: IF I had heard the name in passing; past conversations with tourist (I work in hospitality) ; If I had been there.
memorable: I wondered if it was a famous city from tv and movies or not.
unique: If the spellig was unconventional to the US.
realistic: If the city sounded American; British; asian; middle eastern when I said it aloud.
similar: I have not done a similar study before
comments: It was a little long. And the option to see how good/bad your own memory was would be interesting to see at the end.
